Here are the Non-Autistic, Non OCD puzzle making rules/protips....

Protip #1:
>Don't be a retard and place all the side pieces all the way around the outside of the work area.
Throw all the side pieces in a big pile and then build them all together ....you shouldn't have to scroll the screen around like a moron just to do the sides.

Protip #2:
>build the puzzle in the MIDDLE of the work area.
Only faggots build the puzzle in one of the corners or against a side of the work area especially when that corner/side is on the right of the work area where it will get covered by the chat/user list.
Placing the puzzle in the middle of the work area allows you to place all the pieces around it nice and close, then if you retards wnat to build sections of the puzzle on your own, you have lots of space left out around the outside of the work area to do that stupid shit. (I'm for building the puzzle on the puzzle, not in different sections, but to each his own on this one.

Protip # 3:
>the pieces are perfectly spaced at the start of the puzzle, but not perfectly Placed.

Spacing is for complete amatuers who have absolutely no faith in their puzzle building capabilities. You do not need to see the entire piece to have an idea of where it goes. If it's a rotation puzzle. than that is different, but for no rotation having the pieces overlap a little bit is not going to slow the building proccess down in any way. In fact it will speed up the process because as the pieces get moved in close to the puzzle, you can zoom in more. More zoom = more details of the pieces. The details are what is important, not the shape of the piece. The closer the pieces are together, the easier it is to tell even slight variances in colors on the pieces and when doing puzzles of nudes where 90% of the pieces are a shade of brown...this is VERY important!!!!!

Protip #4
>don't jack off until the puzzle is complete.
There should be a mandatory circle jerk at the end of every puzzle.
